# English Documentation Standard

## Context

- When working with any Product Requirement Document (PRD)
- When creating or editing architecture documents
- When establishing project documentation that needs to be shared across teams
- When creating documentation that will be referenced in code or technical contexts

## Critical Rules

- ALL documentation for PRDs and architecture MUST be written in English
- Headings, descriptions, requirements, and all content must be English
- Code examples and references in documentation must be in English
- Only UI-specific content may be in non-English languages when required for the end-user
- Technical terms should follow industry-standard English terminology
- Translation must be provided immediately if non-English content is necessary for business context
- Diagrams must have English labels and descriptions

